í°§ Introduction to Linux

Linux is an open-source, Unix-like operating system kernel created by Linus Torvalds in 1991. Today, it powers everything from servers and supercomputers to smartphones (like Android) and embedded systems.

Popular Linux distributions (distros) include:

Ubuntu
Fedora
Debian
Arch Linux

